  "issue": {
    "title": "clang is suboptimal for `(a % b) lt/ge (b-1)` where b is a power of 2",
    "body": "Example-1 (b=512, \"less than\")\r\nhttps://godbolt.org/z/Tdc6onb6e\r\nhttps://alive2.llvm.org/ce/z/wvSEvC\r\n```cpp\r\nint foo(int a)\r\n{\r\n   return (a % 512) < 511;\r\n}\r\n\r\nint bar(int a)\r\n{\r\n   return (a & -2147483137) != 511;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nExample-2 (b=8, \"greater than or equal to\")\r\nhttps://godbolt.org/z/cxdveoT1n\r\nhttps://alive2.llvm.org/ce/z/sm3xs5\r\n```cpp\r\nint baz(int a)\r\n{\r\n   return (a % 8) >= 7;\r\n}\r\n\r\nint qux(int a)\r\n{\r\n   return (a & -2147483641) == 7;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n",
    "author": "k-arrows",
    "labels": [
      "llvm:instcombine",
      "missed-optimization"
    ],
    "comments": [
      {
        "author": "elhewaty",
        "body": "I will  work on this."
      },
      {
        "author": "elhewaty",
        "body": "I think it needs to be fixed for all types: https://godbolt.org/z/z8r76q451"
      },
      {
        "author": "elhewaty",
        "body": "@RKSimon  for the X86_64 generated code here: https://godbolt.org/z/sTrsj1aW4, is it better to use `-2147483641` instead of `-121`?"
      },
      {
        "author": "RKSimon",
        "body": "> @RKSimon for the X86_64 generated code here: https://godbolt.org/z/sTrsj1aW4, is it better to use `-2147483641` instead of `-121`?\r\n\r\n-121 is better as it can be represented with a 8-bit (sign extended) constant encoding: https://godbolt.org/z/esG3r7773"
      }
    ]
  },
  "properties": {
    "is_single_file_fix": true,
    "is_single_func_fix": false
  }
}